Is the computer trying to boot on something? Or does it simply restart everytime it starts up?
Does it stop after you've done this a couple of times, or is there no way of entering the PC?
If you have not tried this, try and get into Your BIOS settings when the computer is starting up. Im not sure wich button Your computer uses but it's usually F9, F10, F11 or F12.
Then when you're in the BIOS, check Your Boot settings. Check out the boot order, is it looking weird? Is the pc trying to boot on something that does not exist?
You could also try and reset the boot settings to default and see if this helps.
Hope you'll solve the issue! :)
